Reference-contexts: To receive the M.Phil. degree, the student must Ph.D. pass all four qualifiers and satisfy the teaching requirement. It is the student's responsibility to apply for his/her degrees in a timely manner. Also, students who have an M.Phil. must submit a yearly progress report to GSAS (see <ref> [3] </ref>). 10.3 Time Limits GSAS time limits are: * The M.Phil. must be obtained within three years. * The Ph.D. must be obtained within six years. * The dissertation proposal must be submitted within six months of com pletion of the M.Phil.
