Reference-contexts: Each of the following areas is covered by an examination given every semester, near the end of a semester: * Theoretical Computer Science * Software Systems * Artificial Intelligence * Computer Systems The qualifiers conform to syllabi (see <ref> [5] </ref> for where to get a copy) published in each area by a committee of faculty. <p> A list of course substitutions for each exam is published as part of the syllabi on which the associated examination is based (see <ref> [5] </ref>). (There is no explicit linkage between courses and areas of the syllabus; however, in practice there is a relatively faithful one-to-one mapping.) Up to four courses may be required, and the student may be offered some choice from a larger list of courses.
